introduction: This video is about a virtual conference that will take place on February 15th and 22nd. The conference will feature keynotes, engineering, and product tracks, as well as hands-on workshops. Some of the keynote speakers include Jason Louie, Shrea Shanar, and Tunji, the lead researcher on the Deep Speed project at Microsoft. The conference will also cover topics such as AI product ownership, engineering, and product management. The conference aims to provide a platform for professionals in the AI and machine learning industry to learn, network, and collaborate.

sections.title: Section 1: Introduction to the Virtual Conference
content: The virtual conference will be held on February 15th and 22nd.
It will feature keynotes, engineering, and product tracks.
Hands-on workshops will also be available.
Some of the keynote speakers include Jason Louie, Shrea Shanar, and Tunji.

sections.title: Section 2: Keynote Speakers
content: Jason Louie will be speaking about AI product ownership.
Shrea Shanar will discuss the role of AI in product development.
Tunji will share insights on the Deep Speed project at Microsoft.
Other keynote speakers include Cameron Wolf, Lauren Lockridge, and Matt Sharpe.

sections.title: Section 3: Engineering Track
content: The engineering track will cover topics such as AI product ownership and engineering.
Talks will focus on best practices and case studies.
Speakers will discuss the latest developments in AI and machine learning.
Topics will include deep learning, natural language processing, and computer vision.

sections.title: Section 4: Product Track
content: The product track will focus on AI and product management.
Talks will explore how AI can improve product development and design.
Speakers will discuss the latest trends and innovations in AI product management.
Topics will include product discovery, user experience, and product analytics.

sections.title: Section 5: Hands-On Workshops
content: Hands-on workshops will provide attendees with practical experience in AI and machine learning.
Workshops will cover topics such as natural language processing, computer vision, and deep learning.
Attendees will have the opportunity to work on real-world projects and receive feedback from experts.
Workshops will be led by experienced professionals in the field.
